comment: Millsap (ATL) makes incidental contact with Ferrell (DAL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Curry (DAL) legally contests Hardaway Jr.'s (ATL) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Curry (DAL) makes marginal contact with Sefolosha (ATL) following the screen.
Millsap (ATL) sets the screen on Ferrell (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Barnes (DAL) sets the screen on Hardaway Jr. (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Ilyasova (ATL) makes contact with Curry's (DAL) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
[Observable in enhanced video] Nowitzki (DAL) never fully clears the lane and is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Millsap (ATL) sets the screen on Ferrell (DAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Nowitzki (DAL) is in the lane actively guarding an opponent within 3 seconds.
Curry (DAL) makes body to body contact with Hardaway Jr. (ATL) that affects his SQBR.
Curry (DAL) makes incidental contact with Hardaway (ATL) that does not affect his FOM.
Finney-Smith (DAL) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Millsap (ATL) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Curry (DAL) sets the screen on Bazemore (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Bazemore (ATL) maintains legal guarding position on Curry (DAL) and the contact is incidental.
Finney-Smith (DAL) grabs Ilyasova (ATL) and affects his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Schroder (ATL) cleanly blocks Curry's (DAL) jump shot attempt.
Sefolosha (ATL) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Barnes (DAL) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
